programme.desc: Tragedy occurs when a Neo-Nazi disputes the Holocaust with the son of a death camp survivor.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Sail Away
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a novelist who's given up. Also, they motivate the man's grandson, who has yet to tap into his literary potential.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children
programme.desc: A reporter uncovers a secret about the past of a woman who runs a home for unwed mothers.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain
programme.desc: For the past 12 years Sue Chamberlain has been harbouring a devastating secret. She's entirely lost her confidence and her youth. Presenter Nicky Hambleton-Jones and a team of experts revive Sue's confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain "One Year On"
programme.desc: Just a year ago, Sue Chamberlain was a 34 year old living in a 40 year old's body. Now, a year on, we retrace Sue's transformational journey – and pop in to pay Sue a return visit. Will she still be looking fabulous – or flabby?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Tomkins
programme.desc: Night shift worker Sue Tomkins has lost her sparkle. Lank hair, haggard wrinkles, sunken eyes and weary clothes are just the starting point for Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of experts who've got 10 days to knock 10 years off Sue's lifeless look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand
programme.desc: Everyone wants to look younger but if you work hard and play hard like Sue Whyte, it's far tougher to roll back those years. Sue's already stopped smoking and lost a lot of weight so can Fiona McDonald and her team of time warriors take care of the rest?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Super-Mom, Super Tired
programme.desc: Three kids in three years, a career, and years of sun worshiping has left this super-mom looking less than super. After hi-tech procedures at the dermatologist, a Pilates session, new outfit and makeup, will this mom look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Taryn Couper
programme.desc: Taryn Couper admits she's stuck in the 1970s so it's up to Fiona McDonald and her team of experts to turn her from Hamilton hippie to boho chic, making her look 10 years younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Competitive Edge
programme.desc: As a teen, Luray used to go from the beach to a tanning booth. Now she's after a corporate career, and doesn't want to look like an old lady compared to the other job candidates.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back
programme.desc: In her youth, Catherine was a wild child punk rocker whose bright red mohawk got her elected homecoming queen. But now that Catherine is a single mother of twin teenage daughters, she feels like she's lost her young, eye-catching style.
programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Make Under
programme.desc: Hair stylist Dawn has a big personality that's hidden her perpetual weight problem. She needs to slim down her appearance. With help, Dawn sheds pounds and years off of her appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Most Revealing Reveal Ever
programme.desc: After years of sunbathing, Stefanie hid her sun-damaged skin under frumpy and matronly clothes. But after a flurry of skin treatments, Stefanie stuns her family and friends at one of our most revealing reveals ever!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Old Look Is In Remission
programme.desc: Bobbi's appearance has suffered greatly due to her constant medical treatments and recent mastectomy. After losing her hair and her left breast, she is ready for a change, and has called upon our team of experts to help her through the process.
programme.sub-title: The Old Look Is In Remission

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Trials of Tracy
programme.desc: Tracy is a New York City lawyer who can't find a man. Her frumpy wardrobe and thick glasses keep her home buried in her books for fear of rejection. But our team is on the case to bring this lonely lawyer out of her shell and gain some needed confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA
programme.desc: Natasha has struggled to get her fashion jewelry business off the ground and lost sight of her own looks along the way. She worried that her tired looks and wardrobe of sweats were hurting sales in a business focused on fashion.
programme.sub-title: This Diva is Back and On Track

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Time to Face the Music
programme.desc: Akil is an unemployed music industry executive who feels like his under eye bags, to long dread locks and older looks are getting in the way of getting a new job. 10 Years Younger is on one of it's hardest missions to date!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Tomboy to 10
programme.desc: Stephanie is an avid soccer player, but she doesn't get much of a kick out of life anymore. Stephanie's worst fear about her appearance is her teeth, or rather her missing tooth and she also thinks her skin is aging prematurely.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: With Danny away, and Du Plessis undertaking an ignominious stretch of community service, Ed is left in charge of running the Endangered Species Project.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Ed are anxiously preparing for a review with JLW, the pharmaceutical company that fund their Endangered Species Project. They are desperate for it to go smoothly, and as a result are driving the rest of the family mad.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Following the loss of their funding, the family are in dire financial straits. Danny and Ed attempt to get an extension on their mortgage but are refused. Fiona spurs Ed on, telling him that the man she used to know would have a plan for survival.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Strange things are happening at Leopard's Den. The family awake to find frogs everywhere, seemingly having rained down overnight; the giraffe refuses to budge from the front gate and the cheetah is off its food.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Thomas and Jensen
programme.desc: The doctors meet nine-year-old Thomas who is very rigid in his thought patterns and finds change difficult. Thomas's parents, Nicola and Joe, want to find out what is causing his behaviour and what can be done to help him.

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Bobby and Jessi-Jai
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Bobby, who won't eat anything except chocolate, sweets, cakes, chips, cheese, yoghurt and baked beans. Has Bobby got a food phobia and what can his parents do to help him try new healthy foods?

programme.title: Born Naughty?: Charlie and Billy
programme.desc: The doctors meet eight-year-old Charlie who can become so destructive and violent that his mum has had to call the police. After meeting him, Dr Ravi and the experts think that a controversial new diagnosis may be the reason for Charlie's behaviour.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Thailand is in a state of political unrest and 41-year-old David, a musician from New South Wales, has just been arrested for overstaying his visa. Can the embassy get him out?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: The embassy is called to a young couple in crisis. Their 7 month-old baby girl, Laney, has died from a virus and they need to get her home to Australia. But can they get baby Laney on the plane?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: The embassy is on high alert after a wealthy Australian banker goes missing. Is he alive? Holed up in a bar somewhere? Or does he not want to be found?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: Jarryd's been busted for drugs in a country where they still have the death penalty. And now he plans to double-cross the Thai authorities and escape to Singapore with his pregnant girlfriend.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Beau was left for dead by the side of a road after a horrific motorbike crash. Now he wants to discharge himself from hospital. Can the embassy stop him before he self-destructs?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 1
programme.desc: 9 tearaway teens swap hoodies for high heels to battle for a place at a major US teen pageant. First, can beauty queen mentor Michelle Fryatt handle the tears and tantrums when the girls reject a dramatic makeover?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 2

programme.desc: Kelli and her husband Riley are frightened in their coastal Oregon home. They are plagued by a headless apparition and often hear mysterious noises that resemble cries for help from the dark corners of their house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fire
programme.desc: Christina has been experiencing paranormal activity ever since her father and step-mother were murdered near Columbus, OH last year. PRS and psychic/medium?Chip Coffey delve into a open murder case and wind up exposing a family divide.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Desperate Households
programme.desc: When Julie and her family moved into their dream home in suburban New Jersey they quickly realized they were not alone.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Laws of Attraction
programme.desc: When Paula's young autistic son Michael, with limited verbal skills uttered the words "Go away scary dead boy" -- it sent a chill up her spine.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Craig-Y-Nos
programme.desc: This derelict castle in the heart of Wales has been home to a famous opera singer and a World War II hospital. This beautiful building is so haunted that the team has to spend the night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Jamaica Inn
programme.desc: This famous old coaching inn has stood in the middle of Bodmin Moor for hundreds of years. The team investigates possible poltergeist activity in a room that no staff member will enter alone.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Croxteth Hall
programme.desc: A manor in Liverpool awaits the team in a place that time forgot. A boy standing beside the fireplace in the dining room and a horrifying hooded man are among several ghosts reported here.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hellfire Caves
programme.desc: The team encounters ghostly lights and voices in the Hellfire Caves. These legendary tunnels were once home to the notorious Hellfire Club, practitioners of satanic rituals, murder and debauchery.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Manor House
programme.desc: The team investigate the Manor House in Ferryhill, County Durham. Now a hotel, this historic house has had many uses over the centuries and is said to house several ghosts.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Mary King's Close
programme.desc: The team visits Edinburgh's Old Town to investigate Mary King's Close, one of the many narrow alleyways off the Royal Mile. Unlike most, this one is long shrouded in tales of ghosts and murders.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Wellington Hotel
programme.desc: The team visits the Wellington Hotel, an old coaching inn that has many mysteries surrounding suspicious deaths. The ghost of Thomas Hardy and his wife are said to haunt the upper floors.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children
programme.desc: A reporter uncovers a secret about the past of a woman who runs a home for unwed mothers.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Friends
programme.desc: While working as a substitute teacher at a high school, Jonathan assigns an overweight girl to tutor a troubled baseball star.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark persuade a youngster with Down's Syndrome to join the Special Olympics.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark's friend Scotty wants to adopt the boy with Down's Syndrome. A custody battle occurs with the biological parents.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: For the Love of Larry
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark rescue victims trapped in a car, thanks to a helpful dog.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace
programme.desc: A man whose son died in Vietnam learns that he has an Amerasian grandson.
programme.sub-title: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: That's Our Dad
programme.desc: A children's-show host has a warm-hearted TV persona but is actually a cynic at heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Tomboy to 10
programme.desc: Stephanie is an avid soccer player, but she doesn't get much of a kick out of life anymore. Stephanie's worst fear about her appearance is her teeth, or rather her missing tooth and she also thinks her skin is aging prematurely.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Tony Goodwin "One Year On"
programme.desc: We revisit Midlands' band promoter Tony Goodwin who's poll of one hundred people last year suggested he was a colossal thirteen years older than he actually was.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Truly A Trophy
programme.desc: Rapid aging as a result of early menopause left Deborah feeling stressed out and feeling anything but sexy. She is sick of spending her days in sweats and wants to feel like a woman again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Turning That Frown Upside Down
programme.desc: Angela's made such a habit of hiding her discolored teeth that she's developed a permanent frown. She's pursuing a career as a comedienne, but it's hard for her to laugh about the state of her looks. She feels like the clock is ticking.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Under New Management
programme.desc: Victoria is a mom and apartment manager without any personal time. Her job creates a lack of structure for her to spend with her family. The Ten Years Younger team will brighten her smile, revive her appearance and open her eyes to new possibilities.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Unstick The 80s
programme.desc: Between her career as an attorney and raising two children, Cindi hasn't found time to update her look since the 80s. She hasn't bought an outfit since her first child was born, six years ago. The 10 Years Younger crew is ready to unleash the team.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Viv Thomas
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 48 year old Viv Thomas.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Wendy Grace
programme.desc: Ex glamour model and air hostess Wendy Grace lost her good looks when she gave up that life for a market stall in Christchurch. Hair, make up and a new wardrobe will all help in the fight to make Wendy look younger but her face needs urgent repair work.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: You Can't Outrun The Sun
programme.desc: Diana is a substitute teacher, but in her youth she was a sun-worshipper and a party girl. Those two things combined have resulted in severly damaged skin. Experts help Diana go from mousy teacher to red-hot mama, but will she look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 24-Hour Makeover
programme.desc: Crystal, a yoga instructor who gets mistaken for her mom's sister, has been chosen for a special makeover. The experts try to trim 10 years from her appearance in 24 hours.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 80 lbs. Down, 10 Years To Go
programme.desc: After struggling with health issues Cheryl has recently lost 80 pounds and needs her appearance to catch up to her body. She is single and ready to start dating again. Cheryl's new makeover will help her hit the dating scene with a renewed attitude.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Budding New Look
programme.desc: When Rose was growing up, she was called "the ugliest girl" at her high school. Even though she is now grown up and has a loving fiancé, those cruel comments from her past still haunt her.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Diamond in the Rough
programme.desc: Dashia is a spinning instructor by day and a feisty tenants rights advocate in her spare time. Our Glam Squad and team of doctors are going to take this diamond in the rough and smooth out some of the sharp edges.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Fresh Start
programme.desc: Dawn was sexually assaulted at the age of 16. Decades later, she's still missing her two front teeth as a result of the violent assault – a constant reminder of the pain and suffering she experienced.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Strange things are happening at Leopard's Den. The family awake to find frogs everywhere, seemingly having rained down overnight; the giraffe refuses to budge from the front gate and the cheetah is off its food.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New Year's Eve at Leopard's Den. Alice has returned, but the stress of combining work with caring for baby Bobby is causing tension between her and Danny. Liv is furious that Fatani hasn't told his mother about their relationship.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Scabby Monkey
programme.desc: Contending with overweight cats and their over protective owners was not what Danny Trevanion had in mind when he became a vet. So when a scruffy, barely alive African monkey arrives at his practise Danny is fascinated by the challenge.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Danny is having second thoughts about the wisdom of uprooting his new family and ploughing all their money into a business venture that they know next to nothing about.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Work To Do
programme.desc: A successful giraffe capture means everyone is in high spirits, until the arrival of Evan and Olivia's real father, Simon, throws the family into turmoil.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Meerly Evan
programme.desc: Evan lets the mischievous meerkats loose in Rosie's room to cause havoc. Rosie is devastated when they destroy an irreplaceable photograph of her mother and rages at Evan. She decides once and for all to go back to Bristol.

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 2
programme.desc: 8 tearaway teenagers hope to become Miss Teen England International. Their next challenge? Championing a good cause. But after a week's swearing and scrapping can the turbulent teens pull off a convincing speech when put to the test?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 3
programme.desc: Behaving like a beauty queen proves a tough challenge for the 7 remaining tearaway teens. Mentor Michelle Fryatt expects grace both on and off the catwalk, but shocking bullying and bitching leads to the most explosive elimination yet.

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 4
programme.desc: The 6 remaining wannabe beauty queens face their toughest challenge yet – a full-blown pageant in Manchester. But with stress and stage fright causing explosive outbursts and tearful meltdowns, which three can Michelle risk taking to America as finalists?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 5
programme.desc: Beauty queen Michelle Fryatt challenges the three remaining teens to survive the media spot light as celebrities – but she didn't mean late night parties and boozing. So will bad behaviour play a part at the elimination in Chicago?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 6
programme.desc: Beauty Queen Michelle decides which teen deserves to be Miss Teen England. But can her chosen tearaway conquer the US teen professionals and bring home the crown for England at the pageant? Prepare for tears and tantrums...

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Nathan is in Phuket on a holiday of a lifetime, fuelled by sun, sex and steroids, when disaster strikes. 19-year-old Paris is on a gap year adventure of a lifetime. But just two months into her first-ever overseas holiday she's hit a big roadblock.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: Retired Army Officer, Ben arrives at the Embassy in tears. His young Thai wife has suddenly gone missing. Rodney has been having way too much of a good time in Vietnam. He's overstayed his visa and run up a $1,500 hotel bill.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: Music journalist, Illario the Lothario, is one of many foreign revelers who have come unstuck. His passport is drenched and no longer valid. He arrives to the Embassy, only to fall head over heals for a dashing Thai diplomat.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: DeLorean: a legend on the race track / Uwe Steimle's "Ostalgie" Classics
programme.desc: An idiosyncratic classic and at the same time supporting actor in three cinema films: the DeLorean. Before being used on a race track, the car is put through its paces in the workshop.
programme.sub-title: DeLorean: a legend on the race track / Uwe Steimle's "Ostalgie" Classics

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Jaguar / Formel V
programme.desc: With the premiere of its first SUV F-Pace, Jaguar achieved the most successful market launch in the company's history. But is the challenger to the Porsche Macan still a real Jaguar at all?

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Historic Ice Trophy / Hyundai / Lancia
programme.desc: The Historic Ice Trophy is attended by many car enthusiasts who don't mind driving their cars on ice and snow. Here, vehicles steeped in history are pushed to their limits.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Lotus Elise vs. Roding Roadster / Planai-Classic Winterrallye
programme.desc: A mountain pass road somewhere in Central Europe. Two lightweight sports cars in a duel: the Lotus Elise and the Roding Roadster.
programme.sub-title: Lotus Elise vs. Roding Roadster / Planai-Classic Winterrallye

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Mercedes
programme.desc: For decades, the Mercedes Sprinter has been regarded as the van par excellence and it is not without reason that it has become the eponym for an entire vehicle class in the German language. Its versatility knows no bounds.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Mitsubishi / Peugeot
programme.desc: Drifting with a four-wheel drive vehicle is a fine art. And nowhere is it better than on snow and ice. During drift training with the Mitsubishi Evo X on the Lungauring in Salzburger Land, we get valuable tips on this subject.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Lada / Seat / Smart / Kia
programme.desc: The Lada Niva first rolled off the production line in 1976. Since then, the Russians have built it virtually unchanged. Why change something that has proven itself for decades in the most diverse regions of the world?

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Toyota
programme.desc: With the Toyota GT 86 from J-Sport, it is noticeable that the company's roots lie in racing. The fans' wish to give the Japanese racer significantly more power nevertheless remained unfulfilled.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Ford / Volvo / Suzuki
programme.desc: Americans like it big and wide. The Ford F-150 is one of those vehicles you wouldn't want to look for a parking space in European cities.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Volkswagen
programme.desc: Now in its fourth generation on the roads, the Volkswagen Golf's little brother is the most powerful Polo GTI ever. It is aimed at sporty customers who do not want to compromise on everyday utility.

programme.title: Tuning: Alpina / Mercedes
programme.desc: Tuning has to be conspicuous - not for Alpina.The B6 is the best example that Alpina has a penchant for understatement. We tested whether there is more to the Alpina B6 than meets the eye.

programme.title: Tuning: BMW / Chevrolet / Audi
programme.desc: The Kelleners Sport 640i is based on one of the most beautifully designed current 4-door coupés. The tuning forge of racing driver Ralf Kelleners specialises in the conversion of BMWs.

programme.title: Tuning: Dodge / Mini Cooper / Porsche
programme.desc: The Dodge RAM is anything but cute. It is a true beast. The ram is the symbol of the Dodge brand and the eponym for a very special vehicle. The RAM pickup combines robustness and impulsiveness.

programme.title: Tuning: Lamborghini / Porsche / Jaguar
programme.desc: A supercharger from O.CT gives the Lamborghini Huracan, which is by no means underpowered, an additional 200 hp. This makes the super sports car the ultimate street-legal projectile.
